The paper deals with the convergence rate of the asymptotic result for the Kolmogorov complexity and Shannon's entropy rate of a stationary and ergodic process. This involves concepts from information theory (IT) and data structures (DS). The paper also discusses the Gaussianity of the Kolmogorov complexity, which is a topic in machine learning and statistics (LG). The use of mixing conditions suggests that the paper may also fall under the category of statistical inference (SI). Finally, the paper may also be relevant to the study of algorithms and complexity (CC) due to its focus on Kolmogorov complexity.
